## State Management

### useState → Public Properties

**React:**

```jsx
const [isOpen, setIsOpen] = useState(false);
const [items, setItems] = useState([]);
const [name, setName] = useState('');
```

**Livewire 4:**

```php
<?php
use Livewire\Component;

new class extends Component {
    public bool $isOpen = false;
    public array $items = [];
    public string $name = '';
};
?>
```

> Public properties on the component class **are** your reactive state. No special `state()` function needed.

---

### useEffect (on mount) → mount()

**React:**

```jsx
useEffect(() => {
    fetchItems().then(setItems);
}, []);
```

**Livewire 4:**

```php
<?php
use Livewire\Component;
use Illuminate\Support\Facades\Log;

new class extends Component {
    public array $items = [];

    public function mount(): void
    {
        try {
            $file = public_path('media/json/items.json');
            $this->items = json_decode(file_get_contents($file), true) ?? [];
        } catch (\Throwable $e) {
            Log::warning('Failed to load items: ' . $e->getMessage());
            $this->items = [];
        }
    }
};
?>
```

---

### useEffect with Dependency → updated() Lifecycle Hook

**React:**

```jsx
useEffect(() => {
    recalculate();
}, [selectedItem]);
```

**Livewire 4 — using `updated()` lifecycle hook:**

```php
<?php
use Livewire\Component;

new class extends Component {
    public ?string $selectedItem = null;
    public int $total = 0;

    // Called automatically when $selectedItem changes
    public function updatedSelectedItem(): void
    {
        $this->total = computeTotal($this->selectedItem);
    }
};
?>
```

**Livewire 4 — using PHP 8.4 property hooks (cleaner alternative):**

```php
<?php
use Livewire\Component;

new class extends Component {
    public int $total = 0;

    public ?string $selectedItem = null {
        set(?string $value) {
            $this->selectedItem = $value;
            $this->total = computeTotal($value);
        }
    }
};
?>
```

> PHP 8.4 property hooks let you define native getters/setters directly on properties, replacing the magic `updated*` lifecycle methods.

---

### useMemo → Computed Properties

**React:**

```jsx
const total = useMemo(() => {
    return items.reduce((sum, item) => sum + item.price, 0);
}, [items]);
```

**Livewire 4:**

```php
<?php
use Livewire\Attributes\Computed;
use Livewire\Component;

new class extends Component {
    public array $items = [];

    #[Computed]
    public function total(): float
    {
        return collect($this->items)->sum('price');
    }
};
?>

{{-- In template — access computed properties via $this->methodName --}}
<p>Total: {{ $this->total }}</p>
```

