## Event Handling

### onClick → wire:click

**React:**

```jsx
<button onClick={() => deleteItem(item.id)}>Delete</button>
```

**Blade:**

```blade
<button wire:click="deleteItem({{ $item['id'] }})">Delete</button>
```

New in Livewire 4 — `wire:click` supports additional modifiers:

```blade
{{-- Fire multiple actions in parallel --}}
<button wire:click.async="save">Save</button>

{{-- Keep scroll position after action completes --}}
<button wire:click.preserve-scroll="loadMore">Load More</button>

{{-- Skip re-rendering (for fire-and-forget actions) --}}
<button wire:click.renderless="trackClick">Track</button>
```

---

### onClick with stopPropagation → wire:click.stop

**React:**

```jsx
<button onClick={(e) => { e.stopPropagation(); handleClick(); }}>Click</button>
```

**Blade:**

```blade
<button wire:click.stop="handleClick">Click</button>
```

---

### Form onSubmit + controlled inputs → wire:submit + wire:model

**React:**

```jsx
<form onSubmit={handleSubmit}>
    <input value={email} onChange={(e) => setEmail(e.target.value)} />
    <button type="submit">Submit</button>
</form>
```

**Blade:**

```blade
<form wire:submit="handleSubmit">
    <input wire:model="email" type="email" />
    <button type="submit">Submit</button>
</form>
```

Declare the action in the component class:

```php
<?php
use Livewire\Component;

new class extends Component {
    public string $email = '';

    public function handleSubmit(): void
    {
        $this->validate(['email' => 'required|email']);
        // process the submission...
    }
};
?>
```

> **wire:model behavior in v4**: By default, `wire:model` only syncs state when an action fires (like `wire:click` or `wire:submit`), not as the user types. Use `wire:model.live` for real-time syncing. Modifiers like `.blur` and `.change` now control when client-side state syncs, not just network timing.

